{"questionId":"15298788","questionHtml":"<p>By solving the differential equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi></mfrac></math>, show that the family of curves,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math>, has equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;is a parameter.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempts to separate variables <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mi>y</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>∫</mo><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Award&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)&nbsp;</strong></em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Award <em><strong>A</strong><strong>1&nbsp;</strong></em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>c</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>Award&nbsp;<em><strong>A0&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></strong>.</em></p>\n<p><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi></math></em></p>\n<p><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;</em>(where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>c</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15298788","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2aiii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"By solving the differential equation dydx=-xy, show that the family of curves, C, has equation x2+y2=k where k is a parameter.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.18—1st order DE’s – Euler method, variables separable, integrating factor, homogeneous DE using sub y=vx"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}